1. Number -> sort ✔️
2. Index sort sorted ❌,  array/ Link lint ✔️ 

```js
const towSum = (nums, target) => {
	let left = 0;
	let right = nums.lenght - 1;
	
	while (left < right) {
		let sum  = nums[left] + nums[right]
		if(sum === target) {
			return [left + 1, right + 1]
		} else if (left < right) {
			left++
		} else {
			right--
		}
	}
	return [];
}
```

- when sum of the two number pointed grater then target so we try to decrease the end of index or point    
```js
sum > target
  j--
```

- when sum of the two number pointed less than target so we try to increase the start of index or point
```js
sum < target 
	i++
```

# Two Pointer Approach

Since the array is sorted:

1. Put one pointer at the beginning (`left`).
2. Put another pointer at the end (`right`).
3. Calculate the sum:
    - If sum == target → answer found.
    - If sum < target → move `left` rightward to increase the sum.
    - If sum > target → move `right` leftward to decrease the sum.


